<rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/" version="2.0"><channel><title>Personal Combined Feed</title><link>https://example.invalid</link><description>Personal aggregate feed</description><docs>http://www.rssboard.org/rss-specification</docs><generator>python-feedgen</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Tue, 30 Jun 2026 09:53:40 +0000</lastBuildDate><item><title>Show HN: A Free AI Visibility Tracker</title><link>https://www.archytasdigital.com/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;It annoyed me how much all the AI tracking services were charging, so I made my own.&lt;p&gt;It's free, downloadable, runs on Windows and Mac, and is a bring-your-own-API-keys alternative to the likes of Peec and Profound. It tracks AI visibility across ChatGPT, Gemini, Claude, Perplexity, and Google's AI Overviews and AI mode. It also has tools for extracting the fanout queries AI makes when searching the web.&lt;p&gt;It's got dashboards and graphs and spreadsheet exports and a scheduler for anyone who wants to track visibility over time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
