&lt;p&gt;# Comments: 0&lt;/p&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48730140</guid><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jun 2026 08:57:38 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Show HN: Mocca – A Mac email client powered by local AI</title><link>https://mocca.run/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Hey HN!&lt;p&gt;I recently built an app called Mocca(&lt;a href="https://mocca.run" rel="nofollow"&gt;https://mocca.run&lt;/a&gt;), an email client where all the AI runs locally on your Mac. No cloud and API keys. The model is bundled and runs offline.&lt;p&gt;I made it as an experiment to see whether local AI has actually gotten good enough to power a real, everyday product and not just a cool demo.&lt;p&gt;Too be honest its not quiet "there" yet but I still think it is genuinely useful for a very specific use cases.&lt;p&gt;Would love it if you guys try it out and let me know what you think&lt;p&gt;Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Comments URL: &lt;a href="https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48729974"&gt;https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48729974&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Points: 1&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;# Comments: 0&lt;/p&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48729974</guid><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jun 2026 08:33:41 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Show HN: Not Another AI Platform</title><link>https://tryhello.app</link><description>&lt;p&gt;I'm 15 and this is my AI workspace platform that I have building as a side-project.
I really wanted an AI platform that had all the latest features like tool-calling, web search, advanced reasoning etc. along with really nice ui/ux - like custom elements for email drafts, flashcards, instructions and checklists that not only stand out from all the paragraphs of text we are familiar with AI but these "cards" or "widgets" are also interactive to the user.&lt;p&gt;Instead of waiting for something like that to exist, I started building it myself.&lt;p&gt;That became HelloAI.&lt;p&gt;It supports the latest AI models, but really what stands out is the richer output formats designed to make AI outputs more usable instead of just long paragraphs.&lt;p&gt;It's still independent and something I actively use and keep improving based on real usage and feedback.&lt;p&gt;I'd appreciate any feedback on the idea, UX, or anything you think could be improved.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
